                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216 M/343.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1912</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department is informed by the agent of the Imperial Irrigation District that
                    application has been made within past few days to the Mexican Government for new
                    concession covering Imperial canal system located in Mexico and it is believed
                    that the application was made for the purpose of complicating the situation and
                    to oppose the interests of American water-users in Imperial Valley. Impress upon
                    the Foreign Office that this question should remain in statu quo pending
                    negotiations of some arrangement looking to the adjustment of the whole matter.
                    The Department strenuously urges necessity of not further complicating the
                    matter at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
